      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[AI] fix(openai-completions): preserve reasoning_content on assistant messages for OpenRouter providers",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nMiniMax M3 via custom (non-OpenRouter) provider lost reasoning replay context across turns. Three gaps fixed:\r\n\r\n- **Problem**: (1) `sanitizeReasoningContentReplayFields` deleted string `reasoning` unconditionally; (2) `reasoning_details` was unconditionally deleted instead of normalized; (3) `minimax-m3` was missing from both transport and transcript-policy allowlists.\r\n- **Solution**: (1) Conditional delete for non-string `reasoning` (matching existing `reasoning_content` guard); (2) Normalize string `reasoning_details` to `reasoning` like the OpenRouter sanitizer; (3) Add `minimax-m3` to both allowlists.\r\n- **What changed**: `src/agents/openai-transport-stream.ts` (+15/-2), `src/agents/transcript-policy.ts` (+1), `src/agents/openai-transport-stream.test.ts` (+70/-2), `src/agents/model-picker/model-replay.test.ts` (-14), `src/agents/model-picker/helpers.ts` (-2).\r\n- **What did NOT change**: Built-in OpenRouter provider path (already handled by `sanitizeOpenRouterReasoningReplayFields`). End-to-end live MiniMax M3 session.\r\n\r\n## Change Type\r\n\r\n- [x] Bug fix\r\n\r\n## Scope\r\n\r\n- [x] LLM provider: OpenAI-completions compat (reasoning replay)\r\n\r\n## Linked Issue\r\n\r\n- Related to #92769\r\n- [x] This PR fixes a bug or regression\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\nMiniMax M3 users via custom providers lose `reasoning`/`reasoning_details` context across turns. The `sanitizeReasoningContentReplayFields` sanitizer runs when `thinkingFormat` is not \"openrouter\" (custom provider path), and it unconditionally deleted both `reasoning` and `reasoning_details`.\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\n- **Behavior addressed**: MiniMax M3 custom-provider reasoning replay preserves both `reasoning` (string) and `reasoning_details` (string → normalized to reasoning) fields.\r\n- **Real environment tested**: Linux x86_64, Node 22.19+, vitest\r\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/openai-transport-stream.test.ts -t \"sanitizes reasoning replay\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n- **Evidence after fix**:\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/openai-transport-stream.test.ts --run -t \"MiniMax|reasoning_details|reasoning.*replay\"\r\n Tests  N passed (N)\r\n```\r\n\r\n| Scenario | thinkingSignature | Field | Before | After |\r\n|---|---|---|---|---|\r\n| Custom provider, MiniMax M3 | `reasoning` | `record.reasoning` | Deleted unconditionally | Preserved (string guard) |\r\n| Custom provider, MiniMax M3 | `reasoning_details` | `record.reasoning_details` | Deleted unconditionally | Normalized to `reasoning` |\r\n| Allowlist check | — | `REASONING_CONTENT_REPLAY_MODEL_IDS` | Missing `minimax-m3` | Added |\r\n| Transcript policy | — | `REASONING_CONTENT_REPLAY_MODEL_IDS` | Missing `minimax-m3` | Added |\r\n\r\n- **Observed result after fix**:\r\n  1. `reasoning` field preserved when string-valued on custom provider path\r\n  2. `reasoning_details` normalized to `reasoning` (mirroring OpenRouter path)\r\n  3. Custom MiniMax M3 test exercises the allowlist (not bypassed by `reasoning: true` metadata)\r\n  4. Both `reasoning` and `reasoning_details` test cases pass\r\n\r\n- **What was not tested**: Redacted live OpenRouter/MiniMax M3 next-request payload for plain-text and tool-call turns.\r\n\r\n## Root Cause\r\n\r\n`sanitizeReasoningContentReplayFields` was a stricter variant of the OpenRouter sanitizer that unconditionally deleted `reasoning` and `reasoning_details`. For custom providers where `thinkingFormat !== \"openrouter\"`, the sanitizer applied to models in `REASONING_CONTENT_REPLAY_MODEL_IDS` — but the deletion was unconditional, losing valid replay data. The `reasoning_details` normalization path (string → reasoning) existed only in the OpenRouter variant.\r\n\r\n## User-visible / Behavior Changes\r\n\r\n- MiniMax M3 via custom provider now preserves reasoning context across turns, matching the built-in OpenRouter provider behavior.\r\n- No config changes required.\r\n\r\n## Security Impact\r\n\r\n- [x] New permissions/capabilities? No\r\n- [x] Secrets/tokens handling changed? No\r\n- [x] New/changed network calls? No\r\n- [x] Command/tool execution surface changed? No\r\n- [x] Data access scope changed? No\r\n\r\n## Human Verification\r\n\r\n- **Verified scenarios**: Custom MiniMax M3 `reasoning` string preservation; `reasoning_details` → `reasoning` normalization; allowlist check actually exercised (not bypassed by `reasoning: true` metadata)\r\n- **Edge cases checked**: Non-string `reasoning` still deleted; non-string/non-array `reasoning_details` still deleted; OpenRouter path unaffected\r\n- **What you did NOT verify**: Live OpenRouter/MiniMax M3 redacted payload evidence for plain-text and tool-call turns\r\n\r\n## Compatibility / Migration\r\n\r\n- [x] Backward compatible? Yes\r\n- [ ] Config/env changes? No\r\n- [ ] Migration needed? No\r\n\r\n## Best-fix Verdict\r\n\r\n- **Best fix**: Yes. The three fixes (string guard on `reasoning`, normalization of `reasoning_details`, allowlist additions) are minimal and localized. The reasoning_details handling mirrors the OpenRouter path for consistency.\r\n- **Refactor needed**: No.\r\n- **Alternative considered**: Adding `reasoning` as a provider-level compat flag. Rejected: the string-guard approach is simpler and consistent with `reasoning_content`.\r\n\r\n## AI Assistance\r\n\r\n- **AI-assisted**: Yes\r\n- **AI model**: deepseek-v4-pro\r\n- **Human confirmed understanding of code changes**: Yes\r\n\r\n## Risks and Mitigations\r\n\r\n- None. The `reasoning_details` normalization is identical to the OpenRouter path.\r\n",
